foundry-kde-theme (1.0.4) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Build out the Foundry Look-and-Feel package into a real global theme:
    ship contents/defaults + the splash (moved from the foundry-iso static
    include) + X-Plasma-APIVersion.
  * Fix Splash.qml's two dead asset paths (background + logo shipped only by
    the purged calamares-settings) -> ForgeHorizon wallpaper + anvil avatar.
  * Re-home scattered theming into this one package: /etc/xdg/kdeglobals
    (color scheme + LookAndFeelPackage activation), ksplashrc,
    kscreenlockerrc, and the wallpaper autostart.
  * Ship /etc/xdg/kicker-extra-favoritesrc (app-menu Favorites: Kate out,
    Blender in) via dpkg-divert of kubuntu-settings-desktop's copy.
  * Ship the LAF panel layout (taskbar pins: settings, software, files,
    terminal, Blender, browser) + re-home the avatar (/etc/skel/.face = the
    anvil) via dpkg-divert.
  * Ship a minimal Foundry Plasma Style (desktoptheme, forge palette inheriting
    Breeze shapes), referenced by the LAF defaults.
  * Partial: distinctive-shape Plasma Style SVGs + deleting the redundant
    foundry-iso theming hooks/includes are still pending.

