foundry-kde-theme (1.0.3) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Ship the Foundry anvil avatar to /usr/share/foundry-linux/avatar.png. Hook
    1100 copies it over /etc/skel/.face (the Kubuntu blue-gear default avatar from
    kubuntu-settings-desktop) so login/logout/lock screens show the Foundry mark.
    Owning the avatar here (a survives-install package) keeps it out of the
    installer-only calamares-settings, consistent with the wallpaper + SDDM theme.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Wed, 10 Jun 2026 12:05:00 +0700

foundry-kde-theme (1.0.2) resolute; urgency=medium

  * Ship the foundry-linux SDDM login-screen theme (Main.qml + background.png +
    metadata.desktop) to /usr/share/sddm/themes/foundry-linux/. Moved here from
    calamares-settings-foundry-linux, which `Depends: calamares` and is PURGED
    from the installed target — so the login theme used to vanish on install and
    SDDM fell back to the Kubuntu "cones" greeter. foundry-kde-theme survives the
    install, so the branded login screen now persists. Hook 1100 already sets
    Theme.Current=foundry-linux; it now resolves on the installed system too.

 -- Will Norris <wbnorris@gmail.com>  Wed, 10 Jun 2026 10:10:00 +0700

